{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nAgents and contributors struggle to discover *how to write a plan that passes the\nplan-review gate*. The existing material is either gate-mechanics (`plan-review-gate.md`) or a\ngenerated, reviewer-facing criterion registry (`plan-review-criteria-guide.md` / `rebar\nexplain <id>`) — there is no concise, author-facing on-ramp, and AGENTS.md mispoints authors\nat the criterion registry for the \"description template\". The same discoverability gap exists\nfor the code-review (`LLM-Review` + `Verified`) gate.\n\n## Approach\n\nAdd two hand-written, prose on-ramp docs — `docs/writing-a-passing-plan.md` and\n`docs/passing-code-review.md` — kept short and distinct from the generated registry (so the\nregistry stays the single source of truth for the reviewer). Make them discoverable from the\nCLI/MCP by extending the existing `rebar explain` seam with author-guide names (`rebar explain\nplan` / `rebar explain review`) via the one shared `registry` lookup that already backs the\nCLI, the MCP `explain_criterion` tool, and the library. Fix the AGENTS.md pointers. Rejected\nalternative: generating these from the registry (rejected — the on-ramp is prose, not a\nper-criterion rubric, and would fight the parity gate).\n\n## Scope\n\n- docs/writing-a-passing-plan.md (new), docs/passing-code-review.md (new)\n- docs/README.md (link both new docs — the docs-index CI gate requires every top-level\n  docs/*.md to be linked from the index)\n- AGENTS.md (fix pointers; add code-review on-ramp reference)\n- src/rebar/llm/plan_review/registry.py (AUTHOR_GUIDES + explain_guide)\n- src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py (_explain routes guide names)\n- src/rebar/_mcp_reads.py (explain_criterion routes guide names)\n- tests/unit/test_plan_review_explain.py (cover the guide path)\n\n## Testing\n\nUnit tests over the new `explain_guide` path across all three surfaces (library, CLI, MCP):\nsuccess for every registered guide, unknown-name → `unknown-id`, missing-file → `missing-file`.\nPure in-process logic (no live boundary), so offline unit coverage exercises the real path.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `docs/writing-a-passing-plan.md` exists and states the description template + the\n      blocking-criteria checklist; verified by reading the file and `rebar explain plan`\n      printing it (exit 0).\n- [ ] `docs/passing-code-review.md` exists covering the commit checklist, LLM-Review dimensions\n      (blocking vs advisory), and vote responses; `rebar explain review` prints it (exit 0).\n- [ ] `rebar explain <criterion-id>` still works unchanged; an unknown topic exits 1 with a\n      structured `unknown-id` error.\n- [ ] AGENTS.md points authors at both new docs; no pointer claims the template lives in the\n      criterion registry.\n- [ ] Both new docs are linked from `docs/README.md`, so the docs-index CI gate stays green;\n      verified by `pytest tests/unit/test_check_docs_index.py::test_current_repo_index_is_clean`.\n- [ ] `make lint` and the explain unit tests pass."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784440311207989001,"uuid":"377ac538-2434-4ae9-a9d7-7612f57dc4ca"}